.journalspam<<
<p>LiveJournal has a semi-automated process for dealing with spam. Please read the following directions to report this content as spam:</p>
<ul><li>If this person posted spam as a <strong>comment in your journal or community</strong>, you can report it by following the directions in <a href='http://www.livejournal.com/support/faqbrowse.bml?faqid=201'>this FAQ</a>.</li>
<li>If this person posted spam as a <strong>comment in someone else's journal or community</strong>, you can report it to the person who posted the entry the comment was in and he or she can follow the directions in <a href='http://www.livejournal.com/support/faqbrowse.bml?faqid=201'>this FAQ</a> to mark the comment as spam.</li>
<li>If this person posted spam as an <strong>entry in a community that you maintain</strong>, you can report it by following the directions in <a href='http://www.livejournal.com/support/faqbrowse.bml?faqid=209'>this FAQ</a>.</li>
<li>If this person posted spam as an <strong>entry in a community that you do not maintain</strong>, you can report it to the community's maintainer(s) and he or she can follow the directions in <a href='http://www.livejournal.com/support/faqbrowse.bml?faqid=209'>this FAQ</a> to mark the entry as spam.</li>
<li>If this person has commercial activity within his or her journal or profile, please read <a href='http://www.livejournal.com/support/faqbrowse.bml?faqid=197'>this FAQ</a> for information on LiveJournal's policies regarding commercial activity.</li></ul>
.

